description: The Chinese government, under President Xi Jinping, has maintained a measured response to a series of US trade restrictions during a politically charged election season in the US. This restrained approach has been facilitated by President Biden's implementation of largely symbolic measures, such as imposing tariffs on types of metals that China scarcely exports to the US.
title: TikTok ban in US: How China may retaliate

description: US Secretary of State Antony Blinken called Thursday on the United States and China to manage their differences "responsibly" as he went on a charm offensive ahead of expected tough talks. "We have an obligation for our people -- indeed an obligation to the world -- to manage the relationship between our two countries responsibly," Blinken said.
title: Blinken calls for US, China to manage differences 'responsibly'

description: Students at Harvard University have intensified their protests concerning the Israel-Hamas conflict, reflecting similar actions at Columbia, Yale, and NYU. On Wednesday, hundreds of Harvard students rallied against the suspension of the Palestine Solidarity Committee, converging in Harvard Yard from various dormitories, where they cheered and erected tents. These protests are part of a broader movement across several universities.
title: Harvard students escalate protests over Israel-Hamas war

description: India's selectors face a challenge with pace bowling options beyond Jasprit Bumrah for the T20 World Cup squad. Will they opt for experienced choices like T Natarajan and Sandeep Sharma, or take a risk with rookies like Mohsin Khan? Even as Bumrah has topped the IPL charts with 13 wickets in eight matches @15.69 at an economy rate of 6.37, the others have struggled to survive.
title: T20 WC: Beyond Bumrah, India's pace options don't look great

description: Spanish Prime Minister Pedro Sánchez denied corruption allegations against his wife but said he will consider resigning after the launch Wednesday of a judicial investigation into accusations by a right-wing legal platform that she used her position to influence business deals. Sánchez said in a letter posted on his X account that while the allegations against his wife Begoña Gómez are false, he is canceling his public agenda until Monday when he will announce whether he will continue or step down.
title: Spain PM Pedro Sanchez suspends himself to 'reflect' on future
Six killed in car-lorry accident in T'gana's Nalgonda
JD(U) leader shot dead by bike-borne assailants in Patna

description: CMA scrutinizes Microsoft and Amazon partnerships with AI companies. Microsoft invests in Mistral, while Amazon funds Anthropic. Both companies respond to CMA's investigation, emphasizing their efforts to promote competition and innovation in the AI market.
title: Microsoft & Amazon AI deals may have a 'problem' in UK: What cos say
Kerala HC classifies Malabar 'Parota' as akin to bread

description: India are placed alongside Pakistan, Ireland, Canada and the United States in Group A. After kicking off the campaign against Ireland on June 5, India will play archrivals Pakistan on June 9 at the same venue - Nassau County International Cricket Stadium in New York. India will conclude their group fixtures against Canada in Florida.
title: 'If you want to win T20 World Cup, I will tell Dravid to...'

description: A daily wage worker, Prijith, hanged himself after mistakenly believing his wife was dead following a heated argument fueled by alcohol in Palode. The tragic incident left his wife, son, and a police case behind.
title: Kerala man kills himself, thinking he killed wife during row

description: Ayesha Rashan, 19, underwent a heart transplant at Chennai's MGM Healthcare from a 69-year-old donor. Supported by family and NGO, the surgery was successful despite challenges. She aspires to become a fashion designer after finishing schooling in Karachi.
title: 19-year-old from Pakistan gets Indian’s heart in Chennai hospital

description: Sunrisers Hyderabad's Pat Cummins bantered with Royal Challengers Bengaluru's Virat Kohli after a joint training session. The two teams will meet in IPL 2024 at the Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium on Thursday. Sunrisers are currently number three on the points table, while RCB are in dire straits with just one win in eight matches.
title: Watch: What made Virat tell Cummins 'You are too good, Pat'

description: A painting by Gustav Klimt that reappeared after nearly a century sold for 30 million euros ($32 million) on Wednesday, setting a record price for an Austrian auction despite questions surrounding its provenance. Im Kinsky had estimated the value at 30-50 million euros but said reports questioning the work's provenance discouraged buyers.
title: 'Long-lost' Klimt portrait sells for 30 million euros
As CPM attack runs out of fuel, it’s advantage UDF in Kerala

description: In Agra, Taj Mahal's city, politics and history intertwine with Dalit influence. Recent events amplified the pivotal role of Dalit voters, shaping the region's political landscape. Pooja Amrohi's candidacy challenges the existing political scenario and grassroots engagement.
title: Dalit dynamics dominate Agra’s politics

description: Recognized as the tribal heartland of Rajasthan, Banswara appears to be the sole constituency across the nation where the Congress is actively campaigning against its own candidate and instead supporting the emerging BAP. Internal disputes within the longstanding party, disarray between its state and central divisions, and the reluctance of the high command led to a collaboration with the five-month-old BAP on terms set by the latter. Nevertheless, Congress' own candidate, Arvind Damor, continues to compete in the race.
title: Bungle in Banswara: Why Cong is opposing its own man
